To model the choice behavior, objective values (OVi) were transformed into “subjective” values (SVi), with the transformation type differing across models. Transformed values (SVi) were converted to choice probabilities by applying a probit function (using a numerical approach, Eq. 5). For each alternative i the choice probability p(i) was calculated as:5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
