				\begin{document}$$p\left(i\right)=\int _{-{\infty }}^{{\infty }}\left(f\left(x;{{SV}}_{i},{\sigma }_{f}\right){{\cdot }}{\prod }_{j\ne i}^{n-1}F\left(x;{{SV}}_{j},{\sigma }_{f}\right)\right){dx}$$\end{document}pi=∫−∞∞fx;SVi,σf⋅∏j≠in−1Fx;SVj,σfdxwhere f indicates the probability density function and F is the cumulative distribution function. Here we assumed that all represented subjective values are normally distributed (N(SV,σ2f)) and n is the number of alternatives. We used this range: [eps 100] for σ2f to fit the model.

This model assumes that the subjective values should be unaffected by the choice-set context. Thus, there is no transformation in this model and the subjective values are encoded as equal to the objective values.6\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
